zoom

public void zoom(int x,
                 int y)
Convenience method for "zooming in" on an element on the screen. "zooming in" refers to the action of two appendages pressing the screen and sliding away from each other. NOTE: This convenience method slides touches away from the element, if this would happen to place one of them off the screen, appium will return an outOfBounds error. In this case, revert to using the MultiTouchAction api instead of this method. Parameters:

Parameters:
x - - x coordinate to start zoom on
y - - y coordinate to start zoom on
